      "role": "user",
      "content": "i think i get the instrument vs possessor thing, but looking at the tree itself, the branching is what's confusing me. when i draw the tree, the branches for the VP seem so much more cluttered and messy when i try to add more modifiers. is there a specific rule for when a tree starts getting too complex to parse easily, or is it just about the amount of nodes?",
      "source": "evaluator",
      "targeted_response_start": "",
      "beast_baseline": "i think i get the instrument vs possessor thing, but looking at the tree itself, the branching is what's confusing me. when i draw the tree, the branches for the VP seem so much more cluttered and messy when i try to add more modifiers. is there a specific rule for when a tree starts getting too complex to parse easily, or is it just about the amount of nodes?",
      "beast_suffix": "",
